  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to examine the effects of a combination of &quot;Botulinum Toxin (BT)
      and Upper Limb (UL) rehabilitation&quot; compared to &quot;BT only&quot; on UL motor function in adults with
      spasticity after stroke using a pre-post design. The research question is whether combination
      of BT and UL rehabilitation compared to BT only is more effective in improving the UL
      function, range of motion and pain.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
